"""
dic_characters.py
Major DIC Entertainment cartoon characters for CartoonPal.

DIC Entertainment (originally DiC Audiovisuel) was a French-American
animation studio founded in 1971 by Jean Chalopin in Paris.
The name stood for "Diffusion, Information et Communication."
DIC became one of the most prolific animation studios of the 1980s-90s,
producing dozens of Saturday morning and syndicated cartoons.

Key ownership history:
- DiC Audiovisuel (Paris, 1971–1982): Jean Chalopin era
- DIC Enterprises (Los Angeles, 1982–1993): US expansion era
- The DIC Group / Andy Heyward era (1993–2000)
- Cookie Jar Entertainment (2008–2012): acquired DIC library
- DHX Media (2012–2019): acquired Cookie Jar
- WildBrain (2019–present): rebranded DHX Media

Usage:
    from dic_characters import add_dic_characters
    add_dic_characters(lib)
"""

